Three women, V.K.H, P.C.N, and L.G.H. trafficked to China under pretext of marriage with Chinese men, returned to Cambodia on 23th August and 28th August, 2014.  
After receiving the complaint, ADHOC sent an intervention letter to the Department of Consular Affairs of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and International Cooperation. 
Recently,received information from the Department of Consular Affairs in Kgang Chov province about two more victims, Ch. N and H.S.N who, after ADHOC intervention, will be repatriated to Cambodia on 4th September, 2014.